name: aloe
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "aloe" %}
{% set version = "0.1.18" %}
{% set sha256 = "0fd48b7dc75669245d4f28daf68930446f33e75732c61f77584d69489cd717b4" %}

package:
  name: {{ name }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record=record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - setuptools_scm

  run:
    - python
    - nose
    - future
    - gherkin-official >=4,<5
    - nose
    - repoze.lru

test:
  imports:
    - aloe

about:
  home: https://github.com/aloetesting/aloe
  license: GPL-3.0
  # xref: https://github.com/aloetesting/aloe/pull/129
  # license_file: '{{ environ["RECIPE_DIR"] }}/COPYING'
  license_file: COPYING
  summary: Behavior Driven Development using Cucumber for Python

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - mariusvniekerk
